I think it may only work on the Amiga Action cover disk demo, but
rumour has it that pressing 'control' and 'return' during play gives lives.
If they run out, repeat the process.

Here are the locations of the secret rooms:

a) There are two hidden worlds behind the main tower, another sweets level
(including a Liquorice Allsorts World, the infamous Bouncing Jelly World,
another Cake World and an upside eown Jelly World) and an extra scrolling
section.  To reach them, run along the ground floor - avoiding the doors -
then go up and over the first flight of stairs.  From the bottom of the
second (smaller) tower, make your way up to the landing above Dr. Maybe's
final door and run left into the wall.  You'll disappear behind the screen
and arrive in the Secret Tower room.  But who is Katie?
b) Once you've finished the bath level, drop down to the bottom of the castle,
and walk left until you get to the small snowman statues.  Jump on these and
they'll turn into a moving platform.  Once you get to the top of the screen,
walk left into thin air and jump.  By now you should be next to some doors.
Go through them for bonus city!
c) Go to the same place after finishing the circus room (the last room before
the end of game baddy) and stand on the golden snowmen again.  A platform 
made of two bonud blocks should float upwards, revealing a secret tunnel.  At
the end of this are even more extra lives and stars.
d) Do as above after the sweets level, but go to the left of the castle.   Go
on the snowmen once more, and at the top of the screen grab the umbrella and
collect all the goodies while you're floating down.
e) On the second teddy bear level, keep jumping over the spikes until you see
a hole above you.  Jump through this and catapult yourself off the bus there.
Once you've done this, get on the higher level and keep walking left, bounce
on the trampoline and collect the wings.  Now fly along the top of the screen
to the right and you should find a different exit.  Go through this for a
special bonus level.
f) Complete a level with does not feature a guardian and you will always find
something new when you return to the castle "selection" screen.  In one case
you'll find a whole sequence of lifts and things (see above) that lead to a
door that you cannot normally get to.  If you go to the very right of the
factory screen and look down you will see a load of crowns, which you can
access after coming back from other levels.
7) It is possible to finish Robocod by only doing half the levels.  A choice
of two new doors to enter is given when the correct level is completed.
Start by completing the Fluffy Toys one and then by doing the Cars one.  ALSO
(the most well known one)  MOVE TO THE TOP OF THE WALL OF THE CASTLE YOU WILL
FIND 5 OBJECTS.  PICK THEM UP IN ORDER TO SPELL C.H.E.A.T FOR INFINITE SHEILD.
IN THE FIRST ROOM DO THE SAME WITH L.I.V.E.S

PRESS 'CONTROL' THEN 'RETURN' and  YOUR SPRITE WILL FLICKER TO INDICATE
INFINITES.

Finish the bath levels and as soon as you come out of the door run suraight
to the golden snowmen in the bottom far left outside the castle.  Jump into
these snowmen and you'll float upwards to the top of the screen where you'll
be met by a door.  Getting through this door is tricky but worth it.  Inside
are loads of extra lives and energy stars.  Go to the same place after
finishing the circus room (the last room before the end of game baddy) and
stand on the golden snowmen again.  A platform made of two bonus blocks
should float upwards revealing a secret tunnel.  At the end of this are even
more extra lives and stars.
@endnode
@node "ROBOCOD 1200"
ROBOCOD 1200

To access the Level Select Menu, type "O.S. FRIENDLY" on the Title screen.
Then during the game, pressing 'M' then calls up the menu where you can
select a level.
@endnode
@node "ROBOCOP"
ROBOCOP

Pause the game and type "BEST KEPT SECRET" for invulnerability (infinite
shields).

Pause the game and hold down the 'SHIFT' key.  Type "ALEX MURPHY" and you can
now recharge your energy by holding down the left mouse button.
@endnode
@node "ROBOCOP 2"
ROBOCOP 2

While on the intro screen type "SERIALINTERFACE" then while playing press
'F9' to top off Robocop's energy and 'F10' to skip to next level.  Try this
one as well: once loaded press 'F3' to access the high score table and type
in "BAMBOOZULEM", then press 'HELP'.  You should have infinite energy.  When
you're in the shooting gallery, don't move the joystick and you will have
1186 targets.
@endnode
@node "ROBOCOP 3"
ROBOCOP 3

While on the intro screen type "SERIALINTERFACE" then while playing press
'F9' to top off Robocop's energy and 'F10' to skip to next level.  NOTE:
Might be a space between the two words.

Try this one as well, once loaded, press 'F3' to access the high-score table
and type in "BAMBOOZULEM" followed by pressing the 'HELP' key.  You should
have infinite energy.  When you're in the shooting gallery don't move the
joystick and you'll have 1186 targets.

Hold down the 'right Shift' key and type "THE DITY MEN" (with spaces).  Now
press the 'Esc' key to skip levels.  Must be retyped at the start of each
section.
@endnode
@node "ROCK 'N ROLL"
ROCK 'N ROLL
Enter "RAINBOW ARTS" for your name.  The screen should turn grey.

        Press 'F3' to get 1 extra pickaxe.
        Press 'F4' to get 1 extra speed up.
        Press 'F5' to get spikes.
        Press 'F6' to get some armour.
        Press 'F7' to get 1 extra bomb.
        Press 'F8' to get 1 extra parachute.
        Press 'F9' to get an increase in map depth.
        Press 'F10' to go to the next level.

To warp to any level, enter the following:
Level number, XX, followed by four digits that when added together equal the
level number, XX, and then the level number reversed.

Examples: To play level 12, Enter: 12 XX 3333 XX 21
          12 = Level number, XX, 3+3+3+3 =12 etc.

If you want to hear the tunes type "COUNTRY"   and a menu will appear.
Another tip allows you to get to level 33 (1 level after the last!).  Here's
How: Find the special hole on level 1.  It's surrounded by 3 left pointing
arrows.  Fall down the hole, and press the left mouse button.  You are now
warped to level 33!
@endnode
@node "ROCK STAR ATE MY HAMSTER"
ROCK STAR ATE MY HAMSTER

Simply type the word "COLBOPS" and then press 'F7' for an extra 100,000
pounds cash.  Pressing 'F8' will make your band play as well as it possibly
can.  'F9' will produce maximum crowds at your gigs.
@endnode
@node "ROCKET RANGER"
ROCKET RANGER

Rescue the professor as this slows down the nazis and they can't use him to
increase their efficiency.  You will waste valuable time unless you rescue
him from the Zeppelin while he is over the Atlantic.  NOTE: In a different
magazine, it recommends that you don't waste time rescuing the professor, as
you'll always be too late.  Instead use the agents to find rocket factories,
and uranium depots.

Shooting the gunner in the Gondola is tricky, the best method is to shoot
below the gunner and move left and right until you are on target.  Gradually
move up until you hit the Gondola.  When you hit it, there is a flash.  Stop
firing and after a few seconds you'll be inside the Gondola.

Find the supply of Lunarium before the Fort Knox supply runs out, so
infiltrate the Nazi base which recieves Lunarium from the moon.  It is in
South America or Africa.  Once infiltrated, your agent there will carry on
sending you Lunarium throughout the game.  You'll have to storm the Nazi base
first.
@endnode
@node "RODLAND"
RODLAND

Begin play and pause the action.  Press the 'Help' key exactly five times (no
more, no less).  Unpause to resume play and the cheat mode will be active.
You will have INFINITE lives and you can advance to the next scene when you
press the 'Space Bar'.  Hopefully you should see a tiny love heart at the top
of the score `nd status panel that will show that the cheat is active.
@endnode
@node "ROLLING RONNY"
ROLLING RONNY

Start the game normally, then press 'C' during game play.  Ronny is immune to
gravity.  He can fly.  Or type your name as "CHEAT" on the high score table
and you will be able to fly and avoid the nasties.  Another cheat says type
"TRACTOR" into the high score table to be able to fly.

Try both of these: Entering your name as "RONNY" on the high score list or
typing in "MICHAEL" when you die at the end of the game will give you the
ability to fly.  If this doesn't work, try pressing 'F9' to get all your
energy back.
@endnode
@node "ROLLING THUNDER"
ROLLING THUNDER

As soon as the digitized laugh has played, type "JIMBBBY" and a message
saying the cheat mode is on will appear.  You now have infinite lives and can
skip levels by pressing '1'.
@endnode
